About.Name: Andres Gaspar Gonzalez
About.AboutText: Hi, I am a third-year student at Seattle Pacific University studying Computer Science. I have mainly worked with C++ and understand the basics of the language, ADTs, and data structures building them using loops, recursion, inheritance, and Binary trees. Currently, I am working on applications programming as well as some Leet-code. Additionally, I have significant teamwork skills, and patience and am bilingual. Feel free to contact me anytime with any questions or opportunities at gaspargonzaa@spu.edu. Looking for internships!

Project1.Title: Systems Proposal
Project1.Desc:
This is my Systems Proposal project. It is focused on the planning, process, and design aspects of the Software development life-cycle of my proposed system. This year I decided on a project manager application and named it Project Soloma.

It has a GitHub repo and more details shown in screenshots.
